name: Drowned god
description:
from the collection of "inside":
Sometimes we die from within. We talk, we walk, we eat. But in reality, life does not flow in us. We are so drowned that we are buried deep inside. We are lost. Sometimes we die before we actually die. But if, if, only if we return to life from this death, we will be immortal.
"What is dead may never die, but rises again, harder and stronger".
G.R.R Martin, A Clash of Kings, Chapter 11, Theon I.
